\section{Modelling dissimilar gas cycles with a single equation set}
Here we outline our "Universal" gas cycle equations, which can accurately emmulate the emissions $\rightarrow$ atmospheric concentration pathway for the major anthropogenic greenhouse gases (GHGs). The equations represent multiple gas pools equilibrating with the atmosphere, each with an uptake fraction $a$ and state-dependent decay timescale $\tau$:

\begin{align}
\frac{\text{d}R_{i}(t)}{\text{d}t} &= a_{i}E(t) - \frac{R_{i}(t)}{\alpha \tau_{i}}, \label{eq1}\\
C(t) &= C_0 + \sum_{i=1}^{4}{R_{i}(t)} \text{~~and~~} \label{eq2}\\
\alpha(t) &= g_0 \text{sinh}\Big(\frac{r_0 + r_CC_{acc}(t) + r_TT(t) + r_AC(t)}{g_1}\Big), \label{eq3}\\
\text{~~where~~}g_1 &= \sum_{i=1}^{4}{a_i\tau_i\big[1 - \big(1 + h/\tau_i\big)\text{e}^{-h/\tau_i}\big]} \label{eq4}\\
\text{~~and~~}g_0 &= \Big[ \text{sinh} \Big( \frac{ \sum_{i=0}^{3}{a_i \tau_i [1 - \text{e}^{-h/ \tau_i}]}}{g_1} \Big) \Big] ^{-1}. \label{eq5}
\end{align}

We now discuss the suitability of this equation set on a gas-by-gas basis.

\subsection{CO$_2$}
We apply these equations in a manner that reproduces the carbon cycle of FaIR v1.0 \cite{Millar2017}, an update on the IPCC's 5th assessment report model. As in FaIR, we adopt a 4-pool carbon cycle, with the pools nominally representing: rapid biospheric and ocean mixed-layer, biopsheric and ocean thermocline, deep-ocean, and geological uptake of CO$_2$ (in order of fastest to slowest uptake timescale). The difference to FaIR arises in the calculation of the state-dependent timescale adjustment factor, $\alpha$. In Millar et al. (2017), the 100-year integrated impulse response function (iIRF100) was identified as a suitable state characterisation, since it is a non-linear function of $\alpha$, and a linear function of the accumulated carbon stock (the quantity of emitted carbon that no longer resides in the atmosphere) and global mean temperature anomaly in an adequte aproximation to the behaviour of ESMs and EMICs:

\begin{equation} \label{eq6}
\frac{\text{d}R_{i}(t)}{\text{d}t} = a_{i}E(t) - \frac{R_{i}(t)}{\alpha \tau_{i}}, \text{~~and~~}C(t) = C_0 + \sum_{i=0}^{3}{R_{i}(t)}, \text{~~} i \in {1..4}
\end{equation}.

